text: State Route 275 (SR 275) is a southwest–northeast state highway entirely within Effingham County in southeast Georgia. It travels from a point between Rincon and Springfield to Ebenezer. ==Route description== SR 275 begins at an intersection with SR 21 between Rincon and Springfield. It travels to the northeast to its eastern terminus, at a dead end in the ghost town of Ebenezer on the Savannah River. ==Major intersections== ==See also== * * ==References== ==External links== * State Route 275 on State-Ends.com Category:Transportation in Effingham County, Georgia 275
